wxWidgets Mutabor GUI

While the original frontend of Mutabor was designed using Borland OWL the current one uses the platform independent environment provided by wxWidgets. Mehr ...

Zusammengehörigkeiten von wxWidgets Mutabor GUI:

Ausführliche Beschreibung

While the original frontend of Mutabor was designed using Borland OWL the current one uses the platform independent environment provided by wxWidgets.

Noch zu erledigen:
remove this file: a character set error implies that the whole file has to be reconverted.

1035  }
1036  }
1037  return wxEmptyString;

387  void MutApp::OnInitCmdLine(wxCmdLineParser& parser) {
388  const wxCmdLineEntryDesc cmdLineDesc[] = {
389  { wxCMD_LINE_PARAM, NULL, NULL, _("logic file"),
390  wxCMD_LINE_VAL_STRING, wxCMD_LINE_PARAM_MULTIPLE|wxCMD_LINE_PARAM_OPTIONAL },
391  { wxCMD_LINE_NONE }
392  };
393 
394  wxApp::OnInitCmdLine(parser);
395  parser.SetDesc(cmdLineDesc);
396 
397 #ifdef DEBUG
398  debugFlags::InitCommandLine(parser);
399 #endif
400 
401 
402  }
403 
404  bool MutApp::OnCmdLineParsed(wxCmdLineParser& parser) {
405  if (!wxApp::OnCmdLineParsed(parser)) return false;
406 #ifdef DEBUG
407  debugFlags::ProcessCommandLine(parser);
408 #endif
409  wxString str;
410  int count = parser.GetParamCount();
411  for (int i = 0; i<count;i++)
412  {
413  // we have a document to open
414  str = parser.GetParam(i);
415  DEBUGLOG(always,_T("cmd line param: %s\n"), WXSTRINGCAST(str));
416  // this will probably see if the file exists, and has the right extension
417 
418 // MutFrame * frame = CreateMainFrame(EditorMenu);
419 // frame->OpenFile(str);
420 
421  if (document_manager)
422  document_manager->CreateDocument(str, wxDOC_SILENT);
423  }
424 
425  DEBUGLOG (other, _T("Command line parsed."));
426  return true;
427  }

429  void MutApp::OnUnhandledException() {
430  try {
431  throw;
432  } catch (std::exception e) {
433  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
434  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
435  } catch(...) {
436  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
437  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
438  }
439 #ifdef DEBUG
440  abort();
441 #endif
442  }
443  bool MutApp::OnExceptionInMainLoop() {
444  try {
445  throw;
446  } catch (std::exception e) {
447  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
448  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
449  } catch(...) {
450  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
451  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
452  return 1; //or whatever...
453  }
454 #ifdef DEBUG
455  abort();
456 #endif
457  }
458  void MutApp::OnFatalException() {
459  try {
460  throw;
461  } catch (std::exception e) {
462  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception: " << e.what() << std::endl <<
463  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
464  } catch(...) {
465  std::cerr << "Unhandled exception!" << std::endl <<
466  boost::current_exception_diagnostic_information();
467  }
468 #ifdef DEBUG
469  abort();
470 #endif

487 // Extend event processing to search the view's event table
488  bool MutApp::ProcessEvent(wxEvent& event)
489  {
490  bool retval = wxApp::ProcessEvent(event);
491 #ifdef DEBUG
492  if (!retval) {
493  DEBUGLOG(eventqueue,
494  _T("Unhandled event %p, id=%d, type=%d"),
495  static_cast<void *>(&event),
496  (int)(event.GetId()),
497  (int)(event.GetEventType())
498  );
499  }
500 #endif
501  return retval;
502  }
503 #if 0
504  // may be removed

508  static_cast<void *>(&event),
509  event.GetId(),
510  (int)event.GetEventType()
511  );
512  if (!(document_manager->ProcessEvent(event)))
513  event.Skip();
514  }

518  static_cast<void *>(&event),

526  void MutApp::OnMRUFile(wxCommandEvent& event)
527  {
528  int n = event.GetId() - wxID_FILE1; // the index in MRU list
529  wxString filename(document_manager->GetHistoryFile(n));
530  if ( !filename.empty() )
531  {
532  // verify that the file exists before doing anything else
533  if ( wxFile::Exists(filename) )
534  {
535  // try to open it
536  if (!document_manager->CreateDocument(filename, wxDOC_SILENT))
537  {
538  // remove the file from the MRU list. The user should already be notified.
539  document_manager->RemoveFileFromHistory(n);
540 
541  wxLogError(_("The file '%s' couldn't be opened.\nIt has been removed from the most recently used files list."),
542  filename.c_str());
543  } else {
544  wxView * v = document_manager->GetCurrentView();
545  if (v) {
546  wxWindow * w = v->GetFrame();
547  if (w) {
548  w->Raise();
549  }
550  }
551  }
552  }
553  else
554  {
555  // remove the bogus filename from the MRU list and notify the user
556  // about it
557  document_manager->RemoveFileFromHistory(n);
558 
559  wxLogError(_("The file '%s' doesn't exist and couldn't be opened.\nIt has been removed from the most recently used files list."),
560  filename.c_str());
561  }
562  }
563  }

735 #if wxUSE_STATUSBAR

737 #endif // wxUSE_STATUSBAR
738 
739  return frame;

847  void MutApp::ShowHelp(int commandId)
848  {
849  switch (commandId) {
850 
851  case CM_HELPINDEX:
852  HelpController->DisplayContents();
853 
854  break;
855 
856  case CM_HELP:
857  HelpController->Display(_("help.html"));
858 
859  break;
860 
861  case CM_SETUP:
862  HelpController->Display(_("The setup dialog"));
863 
864  break;
865 
866  case CM_HELPHANDBOOK:
867  HelpController->Display(_("manual.html"));
868 
869  break;
870 
871  case CM_HELPREFERENCE:
872  HelpController->Display(_("reference.html"));
873 
874  break;
875 
876  case CM_HELPONHELP:
877  HelpController->Display(_("Help window"));
878 
879  break;
880 
881  case CM_HELPCOMMON:
882  HelpController->DisplayContents();
883 
884  break;
885 
886  case CM_HELPSEARCH: {
887  wxString key = wxGetTextFromUser(_("Search for?"),
888  _("Search help for keyword"),
889  wxEmptyString,
890  GetTopWindow());
891 
892  if (! key.IsEmpty())
893  HelpController->KeywordSearch(key);
894  }
895 
896  break;
897  }
898  }
899 
901  void CmError(wxCommandEvent& event) {
902  mutabor::error_type type = (mutabor::error_type) event.GetInt();
903  wxString heading;
904  int style;
905  switch (type) {
906  case mutabor::warning:
907  case mutabor::compiler_warning:
908  case mutabor::runtime_warning:
909  style = wxICON_WARNING;
910  break;
911  case mutabor::error:
912  case mutabor::internal_error:
913  case mutabor::compiler_error:
914  case mutabor::runtime_error:
915  default:
916  style = wxICON_ERROR;
917  break;
918  }
919 #if wxCHECK_VERSION(2,9,0)
920  heading = to_string(type);
921 #else
922  heading = wxString::FromUTF8(to_string(type));
923 #endif
924  wxMessageBox(event.GetString(),heading,wxOK | style);
925  }

927 
928  void MutApp::CmQuit (wxCommandEvent& event)
929  {
930  TRACE;
931 
932  SetExitOnFrameDelete(true);
933  // Exit();
934 
935  if (quitting) return;
936 
937  quitting = true;
938  event.Skip(false);
939 
940 
941  wxWindow * window;
942  SetTopWindow(NULL);
943 
944  // if (frames.empty()) {
945  if ((window = GetTopWindow()) == NULL) {
946  DEBUGLOG (other, _T("No Frames."));
947  quitting = false;
948  ExitMainLoop();
949  return;
950  }
951 
952  // first check whether docmanager allows quitting
953  if (!document_manager->Clear(false))
954  {
955  quitting = false;
956  return;
957  }
958 
959 
960  DEBUGLOG (other, _T("Starting Loop"));
961 
962 /* while (Pending())
963  Dispatch();
964 
965 
966  DEBUGLOG (other, _T("Dispatched all events"));
967 
968  wxIdleMode imode = wxIdleEvent::GetMode();
969  wxIdleEvent::SetMode(wxIDLE_PROCESS_ALL);
970 */
971 
972  Yield();
973 
974  /* make a copy of the top level window list as the
975  list may change or not, this depends on actions, we
976  don't have control over */
977  wxWindowList frames = wxTopLevelWindows;
978 
979  for (wxWindowList::iterator i = frames.begin();
980  i!= frames.end();
981  i++) {
982  wxWindow * window = *i;
983  if (wxTopLevelWindows.Find(window) == NULL)
984  continue;
985  if (! window->Close()) {
986 // wxIdleEvent::SetMode(imode);
987  quitting = false;
988  return;
989  }
990  Yield();
991  }
992 
993  DEBUGLOG (other, _T("finished loop"));
994  }

998  wxString MutApp::GetResourceName(const wxString & file)
999  {
1000 #ifdef MUTABOR_TEST
1001  wxFileName rcname(file);
1002  wxString dir = rcname.GetPath();
1003  wxChar sep = rcname.GetPathSeparator();
1004  if (dir.empty())
1005  rcname.SetPath(srcdir);
1006  else
1007  rcname.SetPath(srcdir + sep + dir);
1008  if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
1009  return rcname.GetFullPath();
1010  }
1011  if (dir.empty())
1012  rcname.SetPath(top_srcdir);
1013  else
1014  rcname.SetPath(top_srcdir + sep + dir);
1015  if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
1016  return rcname.GetFullPath();
1017  }
1018  rcname.SetPath(mutString(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/"));
1019  if (dir.empty())
1020  rcname.SetPath(mutString(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/"));
1021  else
1022  rcname.SetPath(mutString(top_srcdir) + _T("/Images/Icons/png/") + dir);
1023  if (rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
1024  return rcname.GetFullPath();
1025  }
1026  std::cout << (const char *)rcname.GetFullPath().ToUTF8() << std::endl;
1027  return file;
1028 
1029 #else
1030 
1031  const wxLocale * m_locale = wxGetLocale();
1032  wxStandardPathsBase & sp = wxStandardPaths::Get();
1033  wxString localename = m_locale->GetCanonicalName();
1034  wxFileName relativename(file);
1035  wxFileName rcname(relativename);
1036  rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetLocalizedResourcesDir(localename));
1037  DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,_T("Trying do load resources...\n%s\n%s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str(),sp.GetResourcesDir().c_str());
1038  if (!rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
1039  rcname = relativename;
1040  rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetLocalizedResourcesDir(localename.BeforeFirst(_T('_'))));
1041  DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,_T("Trying %s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str());
1042  if (!rcname.IsFileReadable()) {
1043  rcname = relativename;
1044  rcname.MakeAbsolute(sp.GetResourcesDir());
1045  DEBUGLOGTYPE(other,MutApp,_T("Trying %s"),rcname.GetFullPath().c_str());
1046  }
1047  }
1048  localename = rcname.GetFullPath();
1049  return localename;
1050 #endif
1051  }

1102 #endif

1404  void MutApp::SaveState()
1405  {
1406  /* \todo save Parameters of all open windows */
1407  wxConfigBase *config = wxConfig::Get();
1408  if (!config) {
1409  wxLogError(_("Could not get configuration storage"));
1410  return;
1411  }
1412 
1413  wxString oldpath = config->GetPath();
1414 
1415  config->SetPath(_T("/Settings"));
1416  config->Write(_T("Tone system"), asTS);
1417  config->Write(_T("Save editor"), SaveEditor);
1418  config->Write(_T("Color bars"), UseColorBars);
1419 
1420  config->SetPath(_T("DocManager"));
1421  document_manager->FileHistorySave(*config);
1422  config->SetPath(_T(".."));
1423 
1424  SaveRoutes(config);
1425  config->SetPath(oldpath);
1426  }
1427 
1428  void MutApp::RestoreState()
1429 
1430  {
1431  /* \todo restore Windows of last session. */
1432  wxConfigBase *config = wxConfig::Get();
1433  if (!config) {
1434  wxLogError(_("Could not get configuration storage"));
1435  return;
1436  }
1437 
1438 
1439  // up to Version 2.9.3 the file history does not cleanup menus
1440  if (document_manager) {
1441  int max = document_manager->GetHistoryFilesCount();
1442  wxFileHistory * h = document_manager->GetFileHistory();
1443  if (h)
1444  for (int i = max-1; i >= 0; i--)
1445  h -> RemoveFileFromHistory(i);
1446  }
1447 
1448  wxString oldpath = config->GetPath();
1449 
1450  config->SetPath(_T("/Settings"));
1451  config->Read(_T("ToneSystem"), &asTS, true);
1452  config->Read(_T("SaveEditor"), &SaveEditor, true);
1453  config->Read(_T("ColorBars"), &UseColorBars, true);
1454 
1455  config->SetPath(_T("DocManager"));
1456  document_manager->FileHistoryLoad(*config);
1457  config->SetPath(_T(".."));
1458 
1459  MutRouteWnd * routewnd=NULL;
1460  MutFrame * frame =
1461  dynamic_cast<MutFrame*>(wxWindow::FindWindowById(WK_ROUTE));
1462  if (frame) {
1463  wxWindowList & list = frame->GetChildren();
1464  for (wxWindowList::iterator i = list.begin();i!= list.end();i++) {
1465  routewnd = dynamic_cast<MutRouteWnd *> (*i);
1466  if (routewnd) break;
1467  }
1468  }
1469 /* if (routewnd) {
1470  routewnd->ClearDevices();
1471  }
1472 */
1473  // emty lists
1474  TRACE;
1475  RouteClass::ClearRouteList();
1476  TRACE;
1477  InputDeviceClass::ClearDeviceList();
1478  TRACE;
1479  BoxClass::ClearBoxList();
1480  TRACE;
1481  OutputDeviceClass::ClearDeviceList();
1482  TRACE;
1483 
1484  DebugCheckRoutes();
1485 
1486  LoadRoutes(config);
1487 
1488 
1489  if (routewnd) {
1490  routewnd->InitDevices();
1491  routewnd->Layout();
1492  routewnd->FitInside();
1493  routewnd->Refresh();
1494 // routewnd->Update();
1495 
1496  }
1497  DebugCheckRoutes();
1498 
1499  config->SetPath(oldpath);
1500  }

693

695  if ( type == wxEVT_COMMAND_FIND_REPLACE &&
696  GetSelectionStart() == GetTargetStart()) {
697  int result = SearchInTarget(findString); // should not change anything
698  if (result < 0) {
699  return;
700  }

714

716  int result =
717 #endif

719  FindFlags().Down(event.GetFlags() & wxFR_DOWN));

721  event.GetFlags(),
722  (const wxChar*)findString,result);
723  } else if (type == wxEVT_COMMAND_FIND_REPLACE_ALL )
724  {
725  // first search is treated different
726  // (e.g. reuse current target)
727  if (event.GetFlags() & wxFR_DOWN) {

756  }

1873  {
1874  /* the current implementation saves unused box command
1875  ids for further usage. Thus the map of command ids
1876  will never get smaller.
1877 
1878  On the other hand, the number of used command ids
1879  equals the largest number of boxes that have been
1880  active simultaniously.
1881 
1882  This set of command ids is copied once per call. So
1883  the complexity of this function can be roughly
1884  estimated by $#(boxes) * max\{#(used_boxes_so_far)\}$.
1885  */
1886  DEBUGLOG(other,_T("MutFrame::CmDoActivate: Set Box selection menu"));

1889  wxMenu * boxMenu = boxSelector->GetSubMenu();

1892  // wxID_HIGHEST
1893  // wxMenu *

1898  wxMenuItem * item = new wxMenuItem(boxMenu,
1899  CM_BOX,

1901  _("This item activates the window of the currently selectcd box"));

1910  i != list.end();
1911  ++i) {
1912  mutabor::Box box = *i;

1914  if (!(guibox->GetLogicWindow()))
1915  continue;
1916  int id = box->get_routefile_id();
1917 
1918  // use an arbitrary command id that may not be a box command id
1919  // maybe CM_ACTIVATE is somewhat descriptive, here.
1920  int command_id = CM_ACTIVATE;
1921  boxCommandMap::iterator freecmd = tmpmap.end();
1922  bool new_command_id = false;
1923  for (boxCommandMap::iterator i = tmpmap.begin();
1924  i != tmpmap.end();
1925  ++i) {
1926  if (i->second == box) {
1927  command_id = i->first;
1928  tmpmap.erase(i);
1929  break;
1930  }
1931 
1932  // this means that the command id was
1933  // in use but is currently not
1934  if (!(i->second)) {
1935  freecmd = i;
1936  }
1937  }
1938 
1939  if (command_id == CM_ACTIVATE) {
1940  if (freecmd == tmpmap.end()) {
1941  command_id = wxNewId();
1942  new_command_id = true;
1943  } else {
1944  command_id = freecmd->first;
1945  tmpmap.erase(freecmd);
1946  }
1947  DEBUGLOG (menu, _("Box %d got a new id %d"),
1948  id,command_id);
1949  }
1950 
1951  boxCommandIds[command_id]=box;
1952 
1953  DEBUGLOG (menu, _("Currently %d items in box menu"),
1954  (int)(boxMenu->GetMenuItemCount()));
1955 
1956  DEBUGLOG (menu, _("Appending menu for box %d with id %d"),
1957  id,command_id);
1958  wxString name = wxString::Format(_("Select box %d\tCtrl+%d"),
1959  id,id);
1960  wxString description =
1961  wxString::Format(_("Select box %d as the active Box for box specific commands."),
1962  id);
1963  mutASSERT(!(GetMenuBar()->FindItem(command_id)));
1964  mutASSERT(boxCommandIds[command_id]==box);
1965  wxMenuItem * item = new wxMenuItem(boxMenu,

1968  description,
1969  wxITEM_RADIO);
1970  boxMenu->Append(item);

1974  true);
